headline: As head of Orange County Health Services, Raul Pino hopes to work well with state
author: Stephen Hudak
sentences: In a 30-minute phone interview with the Orlando Sentinel, Pino, now head of Orange County Health Services, addressed a wide range of topics, including his relationship with the Florida Department of Health; his two-month involuntary leave from his state post; and health challenges facing Orange County.

Ron DeSantis, a Republican whose vocal opposition to face masking and COVID-19 vaccination mandates were often at odds with Pinos personal views and those of Orange County Mayor Jerry Demings, a Democrat and his new boss.
